<title>Appendix I</title></head> 



 <H3>  Appendix I</h3> 
 <h2>United States Depository Libraries</h2>

 Here is a list of federal regional depository libraries,  so-called super libraries.  These libraries have incredible resources you can use to  find people all over the country. Some of the items you will find  in these libraries include: 

 <ul>
 <LI> Criss-cross directories
 <LI> CD-ROM databases of the National Death Registry
 <LI> Genealogy resources
 <LI> Business and employer directories
 <LI> Federal, state and local government directories
 </ul>

 There undoubtedly will be other resources available there  that will help you in your search. Make friends with the  reference librarians on the staff. They will be able to guide you  to the resources you need to find your missing person.<p> 

