Title: Cacophonic Convergence
Link: <mailto:pattimcc>; rev="Made"
</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>Cacophonic Convergence</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff"><center><img border=0 src="../../facsnet_grafix/report_tools/sidebar1.gif"
alt="Sidebar: ">
<br>

<h1>Cacophonic Convergence</h1></center><hr>Digital electronics has enormously increased communications capacity, and every pipeline transmitting information can now deliver far more, thousands of times more. Some of the results:
<br>
<ul>
<br>

<li>New technologies are in development, such as LMDS (cellular television) and LEOs (low earth orbit satellite telephone service), and PCS (personal communications services, the next generation of cellular telephones).
<br>

<li>Telephone companies want to supply video service.
<br>

<li>Cable companies want to supply telephone service.
<br>

<li>Wireless telephone firms want to bypass the local telephone exchange.
<br>

<li>Satellites offer to compete with wireline, wireless telephone, and are providing video service.
<br>

<li>MMDS (wireless cable) is competing with cable, and would like to compete with telephones.
<br>

<li>There are new twists on old spectrum, such as ESMR (digitizing taxi dispatch radio grids to provide sufficient extra capacity for cell phone service).</ul>

<br>

<br>

<br>
<hr><center><h3>Return to <a href="../../report_tools/newsbackgrounders/back5.html#sidebar">Regulating the Digital Explosion</h3></center></html>

<br>
<br>
<center>
<a href="http://www.facsnet.org/navigation.map">
<IMG  border=0 Align=Top SRC="http://www.facsnet.org/facsnet_grafix/splash/navigation_bar.gif" ISMAP></a><br>
