<h2>Books and Articles on Crisis Management and Tampering</h2>

<br>

<h3>Books on Crisis</h3>

Andriole, Stephen J., ed., , <i>Corporate Crisis Management</i>, 
Princeton, NJ:   Petrocelli Books, 
1985.<p>

Fink, Steven  <i>Crisis Management: Planning for the Inevitable</i>. New 
York:   American Management 
Association, 1986.<p>

Mitroff, Ian I., & Silmann, Ralph H.  <i>Corporate Tragedies-Product 
Tampering and Other 
Catastrophies</i>.    New York:   Praeger Special Studies/Praeger 
Scientific, CBS Education and    
Professional Publishers, 1984.<p>

Rosette, Jack  <i>Improving Tamper Evident Packaging</i>,   Technomic 
Publishing, 1992.<p>

Stilwell, Joseph E., Canty, R. Claire, <p>

Kopf, Peter W.  & Montrone, Anthony M.     <i>Packaging for the 
Environment</i>, 1991.

<h3>Legal Aspects of Tampering Articles</h3><p>

Goerth, Charles R.   "The Legal Impact," <i>Packaging Digest</i>, October 
1988, 32.<p>

Lance, David  "Product Tampering," <i>FBI Law Enforcement Bulletin</i>,   
April 1988, 20-23.<p>

Morgan, Fred W.   "Tampered Goods: Legal Developments and Marketing     
Guidelines,"   <i>Journal of 
Marketing</i>, April 1988, 87.<p>

Nudell, Mayer & Antokol, Norman  Contingency Planning for Terrorism: Part 
2.   <i>Risk 
Management</i>. August 1986. p. 35.<p>

Roberts, Kenneth A.   "Anatomy of a Defect: Exploring the Outer Limits of 
a     Manufacturer's Liability for 
Criminally Tampered Products,"   <i>Pacific Law Journal</i> 14 (July 
1987) 1173-1214.

<h3>Articles on Packaging Aspects of Tampering</h3><p>

Lockhart, High E., Richmond, Michael, & Sneden, John   "Tamper Resistant 
Packaging: Is it Really?"   
<i>Packaging Engineering</i>, June 1983,515.<p>

Stilwell E.J., Rudolph, S.E., & Arthur D. Little, Inc.   "The Realities 
of Tamper-Evident 
Packaging."(Presentation, Tepcon 88 Packaging Conference, Chicago, Ill., 
27-28 April 1988).

<h3>Articles on Decision Aiding Software to Reduce Corporate 
Vulnerability to Crisis</h3><p>

Thompson, W.A., Smart, C.F., & Vertinski, I.B.    "A Cross Impact 
Simulation of Corporate Susceptibility 
to Crisis: The Case for Organizational Reform,"    Proceedings, Winter 
Simulation Conference,    IEEE, 
1980.<p>

Smart, C.F., & Vertinski, I.B.    "Diagnosing Corporate Effectiveness to 
Crisis," Journal of Business 
Administration, 1978, 9 (2), pp. 57-96.

<h3>Government Crisis Background Books and Articles on Terrorism: 
Bombing, Kidnapping, 
Extortion</h3><p>

United States Department of State, Office of the   Ambassador at Large 
for Counter-Terrorism.   Patterns of 
Global Terrorism: U.S. Government    Printing Office. Washington, January 
1990.<p>

United States Department of State, Bureau of Public   Affairs and office 
of Public Communication. 
Editorial   Division.    

Bremer, L. Paul III. <i>Terrorism: Its Evolving Nature</i>.    Editor: 
Sharon R. Hayes.   Washington D.C. 
Current Policy no 1151. United States Department of Justice, Drug 
Enforcement  Administration Terrorism:   
Avoidance and Survival.  U.S. Government Printing Office, Washington.<p>

United States Department of State, Bureau of    Diplomatic Security, 
Diplomatic  SecurityÕs Threat   
Analysis Division.     "Significant Incidents of Political Violence 
Against    Americans": Washington: GPO, 1989.

