<h3>Journalists' Guidelines</h3>
 <h2>Domestic and International Coverage Sources</h2>
 
<br clear>

<h3>Crisis Management</h3>

<b>Deborah Lowe</b><br>
 Ph.D., Associate Professor of Marketing, San Francisco State University, 
School of 
Business/Department of Marketing, 1600 Holloway, San Francisco, CA 94132<br>
 <b>Phone</b>: Phone: 415-338-1397 <br>
Department of Marketing, Business: 415-621-2583<br>
 Dr. Lowe has ten years experience researching and consulting in crisis 
management 
planning and specializes in crisis planning for companies dealing with 
marketplace 
terrorism. She is presently researching and writing on international and 
domestic crises 
that face business, including marketplace terrorism. She has published 
the following 
articles: "Managing Marketplace Terrorism: Trade Associations Forge New 
Business/Government Partnerships," School of Business Journal, 1992. 
"Terrorism 
Against Business: Executive Crisis Communications Choices," School of 
Business 
Journal, 1991. "Crisis Management Marketing for Tampering: Strategies for 
Domestic 
and International Marketplace Terrorism," School of Business Journal, 
1990. Doctoral 
dissertation: "The Development of Corporate Management Responses to 
Incidents of 
Consumer Product Tampering in the Food and Pharmaceutical Industries."<p>

<b>Tom Cashman</b><br>
 Ph.D., Interactive Corporate Learning, 180 McNear Drive, San Rafael, CA 
94901<br>
 <b>Phone</b>: 415-457-7594<br>
 Dr. Cashman is an expert on computer-aided crisis scenarios. He conducts 
interactive 
seminars for corporations on a variety of business topics. Dr. Cashmans 
doctoral 
dissertation: "End User Computing Risk Assessment."<p>

<h3>Legal Experts</h3>

<b>Eric Greenberg, J.D.</b><br>
 Bullwinkel Law Associates, 19 S. La Salle Street, Suite 1300, Chicago, 
IL 60603<br>
 <b>Phone</b>: 312-201-0777  <b>Fax</b>: 312-201-0737<br>
 Mr. Greenberg is a partner with the Chicago law firm of Bullwinkel 
Partners, Ltd., and 
writes "The Legal Impact"  a monthly column for Packaging Digest. He is a 
Cornell Law 
School graduate and a specialist in food and drug law and litigation. He 
is a member of 
the Chicago, Illinois and American Bar Associations. The attorneys at 
Bullwinkel 
Partners represent domestic and foreign companies that operate in 
highly-regulated 
technical industries, especially manufacturers, packagers, and 
distributors of foods, drugs, 
medical devices, and other industrial and consumer products. The 
attorneys work in a 
broad spectrum of regulatory environments, including the FDA, the EPA, 
the Consumer 
Product Safety Commission, the Patent and Trademark Office, the Internal 
Revenue 
Service and a variety of other federal, state and local agencies, as well 
as Federal and 
State Courts.<p>

<h3>Packaging Experts</h3>

