MI 48824-
1223<br>
 <b>Phone</b>: 517-355-3604<br>
 Dr. Lockhart is an expert in tampering research and is currently working 
on testing a 
series of tamper evident features to determine which ones might be 
evident to consumers 
in the marketplace. He has written numerous articles including the 
landmark article, 
"Tamper-Evident Packaging, How Safe is it Really," with Dr. Lockhart, 
Michael 
Richmond and John Sneden, Packaging Engineering. June 1983.<p>

<b>E. Joseph Stilwell</b><br>
 Director, Packaging, Product Tampering Lab, Arthur D. Little Inc., Acorn 
Park, 
Cambridge, MA 02190<br>
 <b>Phone</b>: 617-864-6770<br>
 E. Joseph Stilwell has worked in packaging for 30 years, the last eight 
examining 
methods of packaging and packaging issues for malicious tampering. Mr. 
Stilwell is an 
expert on the complex issues involving packaging which include 
tamper-evidence, 
consumer perception, security issues, and reducing vulnerability for the 
company and for 
the products being targeted. Stilwell has written Packaging for the 
Environment, 1991, by 
E. Joseph Stilwell, Claire Canty, Peter W. Kopf and Anthony  M. Montrone. 
The book 
assesses packaging technologies for environmental impact and examines the 
prospects for 
solutions. In addition, Mr. Stilwell has written several articles for 
trade journals on the 
issues surrounding packaging and tampering.<p>

