<HEAD><TITLE>Site & Page Accesses</TITLE></HEAD> 

<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link=#0000FF vlink=#52188c alink=#ff0000>

<br>
<center>
<font size="+2">College of Agriculture</font><br>
<font size="+3"><b>Site &amp; Page Accesses</b></font>

<br>
<table width=500>
<tr><td>
<font size="+1"><b>Site Accesses</b></font><br><br>
<dd>Represents the number of times that the site (area) being tracked has been accessed or "hit" from external locations.  This includes hits resulting from being linked to from external sites, jumping from one area to another, and manually opening a connection to the site (area).  Only the initial hit is recorded, browsing internally linked documents within the site (area) does not increase the number.<p></td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font size="+1"><b>Page Accesses</b></font><br><br>
<dd>Represents the number of pages that have been read from the site (area) being tracked.  Unlike site accesses, this number tracks ALL pages read from the site (area) <font size="-1">(or at least those pages that have been coded to track)</font>.<br>
</td></tr></table>
<hr width=125>
<table width=500>
<tr><td><font size="+1">Currently tracked sites (areas) include:</font></td></tr>
</table>
<table width=500 border=1>
<tr>
<td width=320></td>
<td width=60 align=center><b>Site Hits</b></td>
<td width=60 align=center><b>Page Hits</b></td>
<td width=60 align=center><b>Since</b></td>
</tr><tr>
