<center><a href="http://www.usask.ca/index.html"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75  SRC="im/uofsLarge.gif"></td><td width="320"></a></center>

<h3><center>Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE)</center></h3>
<br clear="left">
<hr size="10" align="center">

<p><br><br></p>
<center>[  <a href="http://www.ag.usask.ca/cofa/pace/index.html">PACE Home Page</a>  | <a href="mailto:PACE@usask.ca">Send an e-mail to PACE now</a>  ]<br>
[  <A HREF="feedback/paceindex.html">Convenient form to request more information or send us your comments.</a>  ]</center>
<p><br><br></p>

<hr size="10" align="center">

<blockquote>
<a name="uofs"></a><a name="Main Menu"></a>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#What is CO-OP?">  What is CO-OP?</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#The benefits of CO-OP">  The benefits of CO-OP</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#How PACE fits into your BSA degree">  How PACE fits into your BSA degree</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#The Work - Study sequence">  The Work - Study sequence</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#PACE Prerequisites">  PACE Prerequisites</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#PACE fees">  PACE fees</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#How to apply to PACE">  How to apply to PACE</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="#The Job Application process in PACE and work term requirements">  The Job Application process in PACE and work term requirements</A><br>

</blockquote>
<hr size="10" align="center">
<p>
<a name="What is CO-OP?"></a><h2>What is CO-OP?</h2>

CO-OP Education is a three-way partnership between students, employers and the College of Agriculture.  CO-OP offers you the opportunity to alternate between paid full-time work and full-time study.  Work terms are generally from 4 to 8 months.
<p>
Co-operative education is a dynamic concept of education that extends learning beyond the classroom.
<br>
<br>
<a name="The benefits of CO-OP"></a><h2>The benefits of CO-OP</h2>
<ul>
<li>Obtain experience in your field of study through a wide range of companies and employers.</li><p>
<li>Establish a network of potential employers for full-time employment upon graduation.</li><p>
<li>Earn money.  Average salary in CO-OP ranges from $400 to $600 a week.</li><p>
<li>Take a break from school.  Experience a working environment.</li><p>
<li>Expand your knowledge by working across Canada or around the globe.</li><p>
</ul>
<p>
It is proven that CO-OP graduates find jobs more easily and have a better starting salary than graduates from regular programs.
<P></P><br>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</A>
<a name="How PACE fits into your BSA degree"></a><h2>How PACE fits into your BSA degree</h2>

The first work term takes place the summer after you have completed your 4th study term.<p>

<TABLE BORDER="2"><CAPTION><a name="The Work - Study sequence"></a>The Work - Study sequence is as follows:</CAPTION>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT"VAILIGN="TOP">

<TD COLSTART="1">Semester</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Study or Work</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTRAT="1">Before PACE:</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2"></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">September-December</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">U of S</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">January-April</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">U of S</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">May-August</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">summer holidays (before CO-OP)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">September-December</TD>
