<TD COLSTART="2">U of S</TD></TR></TABLE><p>

<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</A>

<a name="PACE Prerequisites"></a><h2>PACE Prerequisites</h2>
<ul>
<p><li>You must hold a grade point average of 65% or higher.</li></p>
<p><li>Must have completed no less than 54 and no more than 84 credits at the end of your 4th study term.</li></p>
<p><li>See PACE Rules and Regulations for more information.</li></p>
</ul>
<p>
<p>
<a name="PACE fees"></a><h2>PACE fees</h2>

PACE fees are, for 1996, $650 per 4-month work term (tax deductible as tuition fee*) (<a href="http://www.usask.ca/index.html">*See University Calendar for official Provisions and Policies</a>).  Fees are payable only if a PACE work term is found and follow guidelines set by the Registrar of the University of Saskatchewan.
<p>
<h4>The PACE office does not and cannot guarantee a placement for all students.  PACE students are ultimately responsible for being actively involved in job search for each work placement.</h4>
<p>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</A>
<a name="How to apply to PACE"></a><h2>How to apply to PACE</h2>

Contact the PACE office to receive an application form:<p>
Agriculture Bldg.<br>
Room 2E10<br>
51 Campus Drive<br>
Saskatoon SK  S7N 5A8<br>
Telephone:  (306) 966-7766<br>
Fax:  (306) 977-7788<br>
<a href=mailto:pace@usask.ca>pace@usask.ca</a><p>
<a href="http://www.ag.usask.ca/cofa/pace/infosessions_new_stud.html">You're invited to attend a PACE Information Session</a><img src="im/new.gif" alt="">
<p>
Deadline for applications for the summer 1997 work term:<br>
November 30, 1996.<p>
<p>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</A>
<p>
<a name="The Job Application process in PACE and work term requirements"></a><h2>The Job Application process in PACE and work term requirements</h2>
<ul>
<p><li>Job opportunities are posted at the PACE office.  You are also encouraged to network and seek out job opportunities.</li></p>

<p><li>PACE interviews are normally held on campus.  To give a fair chance to both employers and students, we typically use a "ranking system" to assign job postings.</li></p>

<p><li>Once on the job, a member of the University of Saskatchewan staff will visit or call you during each work term.</li></p>

<p><li>During each work term you will be asked to produce a "work term report".</li></p>

</ul>
<hr size="10" align="center">

