<center><a href="http://www.usask.ca/index.html"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75  SRC="im/uofsLarge.gif"></td><td width="320"></a></center>

<h3><center>Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE)</center></h3>
<br clear="left">

<hr size="10" align="center">

<p><br><br></p>
<center>[  <a href="http://www.ag.usask.ca/cofa/pace/index.html">PACE Home Page</a>  | <a href="mailto:PACE@usask.ca">Send an e-mail to PACE now</a>]  <br>
[<A HREF="feedback/paceindex.html">Convenient form to request more information or send us your comments.</a>]</center>
<p><br><br></p>

<hr size="10" align="center">

<h1>PACE Employer Guide</h1>
    
The College of Agriculture at the University of Saskatchewan has carried out a major curriculum review in order to introduce the new Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE), as part of the Bachelor of Science in Agriculture degree, starting in January 1996.
<p></p>
<a name="uofs"></a><BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE>

<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#CO-OP">Co-operative Education</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#OBJECTIVE">PACE Objective</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#BENEFITS">The benefits to you, the employer</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#SUMMARY">Participating in PACE - A Summary</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#QUESTIONS">Answers to frequently asked questions</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><A HREF="#AVAILABILITY">Student availability and duration of work terms</A><br>
<IMG SRC="im/linkball.gif" alt="-"><a href="http://www.ag.usask.ca/cofa/pace/placement.html">1997 Summer Placement information</a>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<hr size="10" align="center">

<A NAME="CO-OP"></A><h2>Co-operative Education:</h2>

Co-operative Education is a three-way partnership between students, employers and the College of Agriculture.  It is a unique plan combining alternating semesters of Academic Education with planned and supervised related Work Experience in business, industry or government.
<p>
</p>
<p>
</p>
<A NAME="OBJECTIVE"></A><h2>PACE Objective</h2>

Our objective is to offer students an opportunity not only to learn in the classroom but to obtain practical experience through productive employment.
<p>
</p>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</a>
<p>
</p>
<A NAME="BENEFITS"></A><h2>The benefits to you, the employer:</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>You have access, <b>year-round</i>, to well-motivated and qualified employees because students are alternating between study terms and work terms.</p></li>

<li><p>PACE services are FREE of charge to all employers.</li></p>

<li><p>Work terms can vary from 4 to 8 months, depending on your needs and the duration of your training for specific tasks.</li></p>

<li><p>You can evaluate the potential of future employees in a supervised environment, thus reducing your cost and risks.</p></li>

<li><p>You have access to short term - 4 or 8 months- temporary employees for special projects or peak periods.</p></li>

<li><p>University students can bring new approaches and ideas and can greatly benefit from your expertise.</p></li>
<p>
</p>
</ul>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</a>
<p>
</p>
<A NAME="SUMMARY"></A><h2>Participating in PACE - A Summary</h2>
<ol>
<li><p>Get in touch with us.  If you wish, PACE staff can visit you on-site to answer your questions and learn more about the job environment you will offer to PACE students.</p></li>

<li><p>Once you have submitted a brief job description to the PACE office, we do the job promotion, collect the student resumes and organize your interviews.</li></p>

<li><p>Students are assigned work positions following a ranking system or on a one on one process depending on the job posting period.</li></p>

<li><p>In mid-work term, a representative from the College of Agriculture will visit you and the student at the work site, for a short first evaluation.</li></p>

<li><p>At the end of the work period, you will be asked to complete the evaluation form provided by the PACE office.</li></p>
<p> </p>
</ol>
<a href="#uofs">Return to Main Menu</a>
<br><br>
<A NAME="QUESTIONS"></A><h2>Answers to frequently asked questions:</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Students are admitted in PACE after 2 years at the University.</p></li>

<li><p>As an employer, you pay students the going market rate.</p></li>
<br><br>
</ul>
<A NAME="AVAILABILITY"></A><TABLE BORDER="2"><CAPTION>Student availability and duration of work terms*:</CAPTION>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VAILIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSTART="1">1996</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">1997</TD>
<TD COLSTART="3">1998 and beyond</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">Jan- (n/a)</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Jan- (n/a)</TD>
<TD COLSTART="3">Jan- 4 or 8 months</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">May- 4 or 8 months**</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">May- 4 or 8 months</TD>
<TD COLSTART="3">May- 4 or 8 months</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">Sept-  4 months</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Sept-  4 months</TD>
<TD COLSTART="3">Sept-  4 months</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P> </P>
*  CO-OP Work Education Term    (13 weeks minimum / Term)<BR>
**4 or 8 months - for same student</P>
<P>
</P>



<hr size="10" align="center">

