<hr size="10" align="center">

<h1>1997 Summer Placement Information</h1>

You are invited to participate in the summer 1997 co-op student placement with the Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE).<p><br><br></p>

<TABLE BORDER="4"><CAPTION>1997 Summer Placement Schedule:</CAPTION>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VAILIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSTART="1">January 8</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Deadline for submission of job descriptions for initial  interview period.  (Job descriptions received after this period will be in a continuous interview period - see below).</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">January 15</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">We send you the PACE student applications (resumes, cover letters, and transcripts).</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">January 23</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Deadline:  You are requested to return your pre-selection of PACE candidates for interviews.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">Jan. 29-Feb. 7</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Initial interview period on campus or by telephone.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">From Feb. 10 on</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Continuous interview period until all PACE students are employed.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">February 10</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Deadline:  Following interviews, you are requested to return your ranking forms outlining your choice or preference of possible PACE candidates to hire.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">February 11-14</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">PACE students are informed of your ranking and job offers are signed.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">May 1-</TD>
<TD COLSTART="2">Work term begins.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<p><br><br></p>

<center>Make your investment in training pay off:<br>
you could keep your PACE employee for 4 or 8 months!</center>
<p><br><br></p>
     

