<title>PACE (Quotes) - What people say about PACE</title>
<!--<link rev="made" href="mailto:PACE@usask.ca">-->

<!-- joanne jacqueline gaudet created this document             -->

</head>


<body>

<!--  -->

<!--  -->

<center><a href="http://www.usask.ca/index.html"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75  SRC="im/uofsLarge.gif"></td><td width="320"></a></center>

<h3><center>Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE)</center></h3>
<br clear="left">

<hr size="10" align="center">

<p><br><br></p>
<center>[  <a href="http://www.ag.usask.ca/cofa/pace/index.html">PACE Home Page</a>  | <a href="mailto:PACE@usask.ca">Send an e-mail to PACE now</a>  ]</center>
<p><br><br></p>

<hr size="10" align="center">

<h1>What People say about PACE</h1>
 
<blockquote><b><p>"As my first CO-OP placement draws to a close, I can now say with validity that the PACE program fills a large hole in university education.  Nothing else can help a person to understand what is occuring in the industry like being a part of it.  Not only have I gained new skills this summer, but I have met people in agriculture with connections for future job opportunities.  It was especially wonderful to work for such a high-class company as AgrEvo and discover some international connections in agriculture."</p></b></blockquote>

<p>Gail Dyck<br>
PACE Student, 1996 group of students<br>
Excerpt from Gail's first PACE Work Term Report<br>
</p>

<p><br><br></p>

<p><br><br></p>

<blockquote><b><p>Milton Weiss is an employer who is a big supporter of the program. (...)  "The students get to apply what they're learning as they're learning it.  You tend to get a different type of student,  a different motivation."  <i>excerpt from AgriFamily Business Magazine</i></p></b></blockquote>

<p>Milton Weiss<br>
PACE employer<br>
Technical Advisor<br>
Canadian Charolais Association, Calgary</p>

<p><br><br></p>

<blockquote><b><p>"I see the PACE program as an ideal opportunity for our Department to carry out some of our business with a new approach.  I also see this as an ideal opportunity to bring fresh ideas into the Department plus we get to influence these new minds that will manage agriculture in the future."</p></b></blockquote>

<p>Bill Morse<br>
PACE employer<br>
Chairperson, Sask RMC<br>
Food Production & Inspection Branch<br>
Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada</p>

<p><br><br></p>
   
<blockquote><b><p>"On behalf of the Government of Saskatchewan, I am pleased to extend my support for the Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education (PACE) at the University of Saskatchewan's College of Agriculture.  PACE is unique in western Canada and will serve as a model for future programs in other provinces and for other industries.  Co-operative partnerships are the way of the future, and it is fitting that PACE is being pioneered in Saskatchewan -- home of the co-operative movement in Canada.</p>

<p>Our government recognizes Saskatchewan's reliance on agriculture for a significant part of our economic well-being.  As we approach the 21st century, we will continue to build on our existing strenghts by focussing on diversification and adding value to what we produce.  I am confident that our province's well-trained and educated young people will continue to have opportunities in this vital industry.  PACE and its graduates will have the necessary skills and know-how to pursue careers in agriculture and be a part of the successful marketing of both our products and our expertise.</p>

<p>Please accept my best wishes for the continued success of the Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education."</p></b></blockquote>

<p>Roy Romanow<br>
Premier of Saskatchewan</p>

<p><br><br></p>

<p><blockquote><b>"PACE is the best of all possible worlds combining academic learning with on the job experience.  PACE is exactly the kind of project the Governement of Canada seeks to promote linking as it does effective partnerships between government, the private sector and academic institutions."</b></blockquote></p>

<p>Georgette Sheridan<br>
Member of Parliament<br>
Federal Riding of Saskatoon-Humboldt</p>

<p><br><br></p>

<blockquote><b><p>"On behalf of the College of Agriculture, I am pleased to welcome students and industry into the Program for Agricultural Co-operative Education.  We hope this program succeeds in presenting students with the opportunity of obtaining industry experience as part of an educational package.  We were delighted with the speed at which the program was adopted and the support is has received from industry, students and faculty.</p>

<p>We are confident that the program will enhance the educational opportunities for agricultural students in an innovative manner and that it will strengthen links between the College and the various branches of agricultural industry.  Together, I hope we will be able to intensify and diversify Saskatchewan's economy through innovation in the agriculture sector."</p></b></blockquote>

J.W.B. Stewart<br>
Dean of Agriculture<br>
University of Saskatchewan<br>
</p>

<p>Copywrite PACE 1996, do not use without permission.</p>

<p><br><br></p>
