<HEAD><TITLE>PAST WINNERS AND PARTICIPANTS</TITLE></HEAD> 

<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link=#0000FF vlink=#52188c alink=#ff0000>




<center><IMG WIDTH=290 HEIGHT=67  SRC="IM/agchallenges.gif" alt="Ag-Challenge '97"></center>
<BR>
<BR>


<p><dd>The seventh annual Ag-Challenge was held on June 18 - 23 at the Western Canadian Farm Progress Show in Regina and at the University of Saskatchewan in Saskatoon.  Ag-Challenge is hosted by the College of Agriculture and the Agricultural Students' Association.  Thanks to all of the people involved in making Ag-Challenge 1996 a huge success.</p>

<p>A Special <b>Thank You</b> the following universities who attended Ag-Challenge1996:
<dd>McGill University
<dd>University of Guelph
<dd>Nova Scotia Agricultural College
<dd>Washington State University
<dd>Universit Laval
<dd>University of Saskatchewan</p>

<p><b>Congratulations</b> to the winners of Ag-Challenge '96:</p>  
<CENTER><b>Overall Winner: Nova Scotia Agricultural College</b></CENTER>

<p><b>CATEGORY I winners</b> - Paper competition
<dd>1st	Nova Scotia Agricultural College
<dd>2nd	Nova Scotia Agricultural College
<dd>3rd	McGill University</p>
<p><b>CATEGORY II winners</b> - Debate Challenge
<dd>1st	Guelph University
<dd>2nd	Universite Laval
<p><b>CATEGORY III winners</b> - Team Challenge
<dd>1st	Washington State University
<dd>2nd	University of Saskatchewan
<dd>3rd	University of Guelph</p>

<p>The continued success of Ag-Challenge is due in part to the hard work and dedication of the Ag-Challenge '96 committee. A special thank you to that committee:
