<head> 
<title>Cankerworm Update From the City of Saskatoon</title> 
</head> 
<body background="im/backgrnd.gif"> 
<h1>  
<center> 
<img alt="" src="im/line.gif">    
Cankerworm Update From the City of Saskatoon</center> 
</h1> 
 
Getting Your Trees Ready For Spring.
<p>There are cankerworms which lay their eggs in fall and those which 
lay their eggs in spring. Both types hatch in the spring. Although 
it is not yet known what effect the spring cankerworm population 
will have on Saskatoon trees, there are precautions you can take to 
protect your trees. Recent local experiments suggest that tree 
banding significantly reduces the number of cankerworm eggs laid in 
protected trees.
<p>If you banded your trees in the fall, check the bands.
<p>-    If the band has come loose, tighten it. Bands must be snug to 
prevent cankerworms from crawling underneath. 
<P>-    Remove cankerworm moths, leaves, etc. from "Tanglefoot". This 
prevents spring cankerworms from using debris as a bridge to crawl 
over the band: <BR>
     If necessary, apply a fresh coat of "Tanglefoot',. <BR>
     If tree bands are excessively worn, replace with new ones.<BR>
     It's not too late to band your trees.<BR>
<p>You can protect trees against spring cankerworms if you attach tree 
bands by last week in March. Follow tree banding instructions in 
the cankerworm brochure.
<p>Important Dates:
<p>     ******** <BR>
     MARCH 31
<p>trees should be banded against spring cankerworms by the last week 
in March.
<p>     *********<BR>
     MAY 15
<p>Remove tree bands after May 15 to prevent the bark underneath from 
rotting.
<p>     *********<BR>
     MID-SEPTEMBER
<p>Initial date for placement of fall tree bands was September 1st. 
Recent experiments indicate trees can be banded against fall 
cankerworms until mid-September.
<p>Protect Our City Trees
<p>Once hatched, cankerworm larvae can travel from unbanded trees to 
neighbouring banded trees and cause defoliation. 
For more information, contact: Civic Buildings and Grounds   
Department (975-3300)  
 
<br> 
