<h1>  
<center> 
<img alt="" src="im/line.gif">    
Dutch Elm Disease (2)</center> 
</h1> 
 
Dutch Elm Disease (DED) seems to be more wide spread than we thought. 
It has probably been here at undetected level few some years now - in 
my opinion.  The following is a list of confimed DED cases as of 
10/10/91:**
<p>- near Carrot River <BR>
- near Glen Ewen <BR>
- near Oxbow <BR>
- Shaunavon <BR>
- near Rocanville (alone the Qu'Appele Valley) <BR>
- the City of Estevan <BR>
- the City of Weyburn and <BR>
- adjacent the Manitoba border alone the old channel of the Saskatchewan River<BR>
<p>** source David Kaminski (Sask Provincial Plant disease Specialist) 
 
